  Claude Archival & Code Extraction Suite

  Overview

A Chrome/Firefox extension (Manifest V3) that injects a floating control panel
into claude.ai, enabling power users to:

1.   Export conversations to Markdown** — Full chat history with YAML
   frontmatter metadata, perfect for Obsidian vaults or documentation archives
2.   Extract all code blocks as a ZIP archive** — Every code snippet becomes
   a properly named file with the correct extension, bundled into a
   downloadable `.zip`

 Installation (Chrome — Unpacked Extension)

    Prerequisites

1. Download JSZip (v3.10+) from https://github.com/Stuk/jszip/releases
2. Place the minified file at `lib/jszip.min.js`
3. Create placeholder icon files (16x16, 48x48, 128x128 PNG) in `icons/`

    Steps

1. Clone or unzip this project into a local directory:

